  "repo_truth": "Fresh read-only review of the exact complete HCM-2.2 ten-times-remediated planning subject. It freezes future implementation contracts but contains no product implementation, grants no implementation authority before clean closeout, and carries no clean-review conclusion.",
  "allowed_scope": [
    "Remain read-only and replay the sorted complete manifest and aggregate fingerprint before review.",
    "Review every subject byte: 00, 04, 06, ten immutable prior dispatches, SPEC, all exact contract/schema/vector/JCS/transcript/API/security-bound fixtures, plan, unchecked todo, planning proof, and ten remediation records.",
    "Read unchanged 01, 02, 03, 05, 07, 08, HCM-0.6 decision, selected HCM-2.1 record/packet/proof, exact live definition assets, and engine/compiler/flow/CLI/skill/template/test sources only as needed.",
    "Run bounded read-only exact schema/JCS/fingerprint/profile/intake, decoded CTAP2 CBOR/P-256/transcript, opaque native-port, user-handle, bounded-input, shared authenticator-use, content-addressed ref/ID/byte, registry-admin DTO, marker/recovery, Markdown/link, Git, handoff, security, bridge, and classification checks.",
    "Return findings first with exact file/line evidence through the built-in channel."
  ],
  "non_goals": [
    "No edits, staging, commits, new dispatches, global handoffs, ledger writes, or user task hops.",
    "No Rust, Cargo, production definitions, runtime fixtures/tests/product/generated-skill/pipeline, HCM-2.3+, Phase-3, SDK, Tauri, Substrate, contract, dock, or publication implementation.",
    "Do not invent alternate schema/intake bytes, fingerprint/ref behavior, approval/identity/registry/use-chain trust, transaction visibility, lifecycle, renderer, migration, compatibility mode, bridge, or sibling-family scope.",
    "Do not treat prior findings, passing reproduction, or contingent planning status as proof that the 47-entry subject is clean."
  ],
  "tasks": [
    "Invoke required skills in order, remain read-only, replay the exact complete manifest/aggregate, and return BLOCKED if any byte differs.",
    "Review findings first in Critical, Required, Optional, Nit order with exact file/line, violated authority, failure, smallest remediation, and missing or invalidated proof.",
    "Reproduce all ten exact schema documents/entries, eleven definition JCS vectors, thirteen complete runtime records including six published-schema validations and a real registry-resolved DER ES256 signature, twelve positive and fifteen negative approver-admin API vectors, seven registration/assertion transcripts, strict CBOR/P-256 decoding, complete 16-entry profile schema sources, dependency graph, fingerprints, old-byte preservation, and independent encoders/decoders.",
    "Verify every security-schema collection and _base64 field is represented by the 29 exact finite-bound groups, accepted limits and one-over refusals occur before expensive or mutating work, and the two user-handle derivations plus five negative transforms reproduce exactly.",
    "Verify caller-intent-only bootstrap/add/revoke/update requests; engine-built complete CTAP2 command CBOR and raw-response-only opaque NativeAuthenticatorPortV1; fake-port no-semantic-leakage proof; operation-by-status/refusal nullability; response-inclusive four/five bootstrap/add changed paths; all-null/empty-delta refusals; exact ES256/fmt-none protocol; admin/quorum/current-pair coverage; and exact native unavailability refusal.",
    "Verify the operation-discriminated registry journal binds and installs the complete response/registration/assertion/state/transition/use-record set; partial ceremony records are never authority; the shared per-credential bounded use head/transition chain enforces full-chain nonce/challenge replay and exact zero/nonzero sign-count rules across sequential/interleaved approval/admin uses; and approval/registry crash, orphan, rollback, and recovery are total.",
    "Verify the full literal sixteen-row intake, schema/retained-field validation value, every leaf source, value-versus-quality-waiver rule, all-mode equivalence, and candidate basis.",
    "Verify exact 72-byte raw-intent-hash markers, total registry/lifecycle/promotion/approval recovery, global promotion-then-registry-then-lifecycle locking, retained observations, reverse-order refusal, authority visibility, crash/concurrency proof, and deadlock absence.",
    "Verify canonical/Markdown byte grammars/fixtures, C03/C04, product cutover, bridges, proof wall, deletion gates, CRITICAL impact warning, planning-only status, primary commit, and separate parent closeout.",
    "Return CLEAN only if no valid Critical or Required finding remains; otherwise CHANGES_REQUIRED or BLOCKED. Make no edits."
  ],
